    <chapter>
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>Welcome to the User Manual of &HZproductname; &HZproductversion;! This book explains
            how to use the &HZproductversion; version of the &HZproductname; effectively to
            transform different type of raster <glossterm linkend="gloss-DEM">DEM</glossterm> data
            to the terrain file format of <ulink url="http://emagware.com/">EMCUBE</ulink> quickly
            and easily. Please note that this manual assumes that you are familiar with the basic
            concepts of <glossterm linkend="gloss-GIS">GIS</glossterm> and its related
            technologies.</para>
        <para>The &HZproductname; is a transforming application for terrain modelling. Raster
                <glossterm linkend="gloss-DEM">DEM</glossterm> data can be imported and translated
            to the terrain file format of <ulink url="http://emagware.com/">EMCUBE</ulink>, with
            targeted local cartesian coordinates. Based on proven Qt4 technology the intuitive
            Graphical User Interface of the &HZproductname; is easy-to-use and provides robust
            functionality for cutting and transforming of <glossterm linkend="gloss-DEM"
                >DEM</glossterm> data.</para>
        <para>&HZproductname; is the electromagnetic(EM) professionals' choice that demand flexible
            terrains for <ulink url="http://emagware.com/">EMCUBE</ulink> and make it a more
            practical EM propagation modeling toolkit.</para>
        <section>
            <title>Key Features and Benefits</title>
            <para>The &HZproductname; offers the following key features and benefits.</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Multiple raster <glossterm linkend="gloss-DEM">DEM</glossterm> data
                        import, see detailed list in <xref linkend="secSupportedFormat" xrefstyle=""
                        />.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Detailed source file information display.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The origin of local cartesian coordinate is acceptable both in decimal
                        degree or DMS (Degree Minute Second) form.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>User selectable rectangular area.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Detailed processing indicator.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>About This User Manual</title>
            <para>This User Manual gives a complete overview of the &HZproductname; and describes
                the basic process of transformation of <glossterm linkend="gloss-DEM"
                    >DEM</glossterm> to EMCUBE terrain file target outputs. In this manual it is
                assumed that you are familiar with the use of your operating system and the concepts
                related to <glossterm linkend="gloss-GIS">GIS</glossterm>.</para>
        </section>
    </chapter>
    <chapter>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <para>This section explains platform requirements and installation procedures. It also
            provides instructions on how to perform uninstall the application if required.</para>
        <para>If you need help at any point during these procedures please send email to
                <email>&HZsupportemail;</email>.</para>
        <section>
            <title>Installation Requirements</title>
            <section>
                <title>Platform Requirements</title>
                <para>Minimum run-time requirements are listed below.<itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Intel Pentium 4 1GHz</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>512MB RAM</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>60 MB free disk space</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>SVGA (1024 x 768) 96 DPI</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist></para>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title>Operating System and Tools</title>
                <para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Windows XP SP2 x86/x64 or later</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </para>
            </section>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Installation Instructions</title>
            <para>Prior to proceeding with the following instructions, please ensure that your
                system complies with the prerequisites detailed in the installation
                requirements.</para>
            <procedure>
                <title>Windows Installation</title>
                <step>
                    <para>Insert the installation disc into your drive or download the installation
                        kit.</para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>Follow the onscreen instructions presented in the installation
                        program.</para>
                    <caution>
                        <para>The installer creates or updates a system variable
                                <envar>GDAL_DATA</envar>. If there are already other applications
                            using it, this action may cause version incompatibility. Please report
                            this to <email>&HZsupportemail;</email>.</para>
                    </caution>
                </step>
            </procedure>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Uninstalling the Application</title>
            <caution>
                <para>The following procedure will remove &HZproductname; from your system.
                        <emphasis>Please ensure that all valuable data is saved to another location
                        prior to performing this procedure.</emphasis></para>
            </caution>
            <procedure>
                <title>Uninstall Procedure</title>
                <step>
                    <para>Backup all valuable data from the installation folder. </para>
                </step>
                <step>
                    <para>On Windows use the appropriate uninstaller shortcut provided with your
                        OS.</para>
                    <caution>
                        <para>All related <envar>APPDATA</envar> data and <envar>GDAL_DATA</envar>
                            variable will be removed.</para>
                    </caution>
                </step>
            </procedure>
        </section>
    </chapter>
